                            <comment id="16968259" author="ancosen" created="Wed, 6 Nov 2019 11:00:45 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Using the kubernetesHelper for this purpose is wrong. This class is used only internally for instatianting the client based on the KubernetesConfiguration of the component. If you need to set your own client and set a namespace, just create the client through the kubernetes-client API and bind it to the registry. Using the Camel helper for this is wrong.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="16968263" author="imranrazakhan" created="Wed, 6 Nov 2019 11:08:46 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Thanks for updates, I think it would be nice if we have examples in documentation or github with usage of&#160;kubernetes-client API, so for novice it would be good.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="16968279" author="ancosen" created="Wed, 6 Nov 2019 11:28:53 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;By the way on the helper the namespace wasn&apos;t set during the client creation, so the bug is there for real. I&apos;m fixing it. I&apos;ll add documentation on the instatiation of the client, thanks &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=imranrazakhan&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;imranrazakhan&quot;&gt;imranrazakhan&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
